meta.description: The Club ATL at Hartsfield–Jackson Atlanta International Airport (ATL), Concourse F. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: The Club ATL

location.terminalDirections: Proceed up to the Mezzanine Level, follow signs to the lounge entrance.

lounge.description: A much welcomed reprieve in the world’s busiest airport. Enjoy attractive, modern facilities in a spacious, comfortable atmosphere. Relax with a fancy cocktail at the bar, take advantage of high speed Wi-Fi, turbocharge your phone through one of countless power ports, and savor a rejuvenating shower before your long haul flight.

general: Children under 2 years old are admitted free with an adult.
Telephone for domestic calls available; International calls can be made subject to payment.
warning: Alcoholic drinks are only available to passengers 21 years of age or older.
Access may be periodically restricted due to space constraints, in particular during the hours of 13:00 - 21:00 daily.
regulatory: Access is only permitted 3 hours prior to scheduled flight departure.

reviews.content: Not enough seats with power outlets.
Good lounge with a decent selection of breakfast Foods and drinks. Has a bar too. Slightly tight on space.
Staff is great, very polite and attentive.  Food selection is basic, but good. Bartender willing to mix any cocktail. Foot traffic was light on Wednesday afternoon.
Extremely polite staff. Lounge was only about 25% full. Good drinks and good food.
Veteran user of this lounge. The staff is without fail surly and sometimes nasty. The front desk person was super rude. The food is abominable and is so each time I go. Overcrowded and awful.
Perfectly fine lounge with a great view of the iconic, vintage “Fly Delta Jets” sign. Crowded, but didn’t have much trouble finding a seat at 12 on a Sunday. Unfortunately, it was absolutely filthy.
Packed Friday at 9p. Ten minute wait for Priority Pass but they brought drinks to us while we waited and then seated us. Food was limited, but drinks were great and staff was very friendly.
About half full at 8am. Breakfast spread was okay.
Super crowded with unfriendly staff.... super condescending at the front desk, not the additive you should expect at a supposedly premium experience aka lounge.
PACKED or I would give 5 stars.
Nice enough place to hang out and rest. Food is under par. Definitely will not be visiting here and pay 40$ per person for day old salad and sandwiches. Way over crowded and seating is too compact.
Food service was slow and when food was depleted they did not replenish efficiently. Lot of people waiting for food to be set up.

Positive: # of different kinds of food and drinks available. Brownies are good.
Negative: Crowded & needed more staff. 2 separate times on short stay ran out of plates and more. Not clean & loud.
Servers were extremely nice and attentive. Food choices were severely lacking.
Great lounge when flying international! Used our Priority Pass to get the family in. Kids enjoyed the gummy bears as well as bacon and bread options for breakfast. Adults enjoyed bread and Mimosas.
Clean and comfy! Friendly staff, too.
Food was pretty decent at breakfast, had your standard “eggs” and bacon as I’m on keto. Many broken chargers however which was pretty annoying. Service was good lounge was clean.
Great lounge, only critique no alcohol until 12:30pm on Sunday.
The lounge was pretty packed while I was there.  Otherwise, it was fine.
It's fine. Not fancy. Meh food selections. But the bartenders are friendly and if you're flying on a non-Delta flight, they're pretty much the only game in town.
Busy. If you’re flying Delta, check out the Sky Club instead. Drinks: no tap beer, decent liquor selection. Food: one soup, small salad bar, 3 mediocre sandwiches.
Extremely friendly staff, especially given the sheer amount of people that probably go in and out of here on a given day. It’s not elite but it’s a lounge I look forward to when flying out of ATL.

This is one of the weakest lounges I go to,  they have a nice bar,  but the food is short of mediocre. They have basic items and a pretend salad. Does not compare to other lounges for similarly sized.
The best service I’ve experienced. The food choices and take away options for those with a shorter layover were minimal.  The key feature of this lounge IMO is the bar.
Had a one hour layover. Traveled all the way from A gates to F gates. Get there and guy tells me that they are full and minimum of 1-hour wait list. Unsatisfactory. Big waste of time.
I think this lounge was pretty good. “F” concourse for FAR AWAY. Super attentive staff. Bathroom a bit amiss. Good snacks. Basic eats. Give 20 min for return trip depending on your gate.
Lounge was super packed when I was here (tons of messy kids). However, lots of decent snacks, food and drink. Free WiFi and places to plug in as well as showers and a business center.
The lounge is very popular. They were putting everyone on a wait list due to max capacity. When not full, it is nice.
Was a short stay, was moderately filled. Enjoyed a nice cup of coffee, with helpful staff member. Lunch had just been brought out at 1310,  looked to be of good quality.
OK lounge. Not a huge food selection, mostly finger foods. Crumbs everywhere from floor to seats. Good service. Needs a little TLC and attention to detail and could go from OK to amazing lounge!
Had no problem getting in with Priority Pass at 4pm on a Wednesday. Good snacks and lots of individual seating for solo travelers.
Great experience. Had a 5.5 hr layover in Atlanta with my fiancé and it was perfect to spend 3 hrs. Great food & drinks and employees were very attentive, refilling drinks often.
Useless, no access to Priority Pass members for another 150 minutes. Why does PP list this place?
Food is not great, WIFI is spotty but the bar is excellent. Amazing staff and relaxed environment. ATL lounges are not great in general, but of the options, this is my pick.

Excited about going to a lounge after for the first time after buying a membership and get there and am told it is closed to memberships for the next two hours until int'l flights leave, what a waste.
Empty on a Sunday morning around 7am, decent food and drink options, plenty of seating and power along the armchairs.
Very disappointed with this lounge. About 11am on Sunday, only food was cereal, snacks, and cheap bagels. Coffee/juice, no bar.  $40, REALLY?! AMEX Plat got me in free...still not worth it. 😕
I thought people were just being tough on this lounge, and then I went there....ouch
Smells like a wet locker. Decent drinks, bad food. It’s way too crowded most of the time. Maxed to capacity when we last went by.
Was closed at 8:30 AM on 3/18/18. No signs posted.
One of the worst lounges I’ve been too, overstuffed with people, low quality booze and food.
This had the basic amenities of what a normal lounge would have. Nothing spectacular.
Staff was great! Food was stocked! Very nice place to wait for my flight despite how busy it was.
Lounge iluminado, especialmente cómodo en la jornada de la mañana, ya que en la tarde hay mucha gente, reponen la comida frecuentemente, la ducha es muy cómoda y el servicio es excepcional.
Full bar with bartender, enough food selections to make a decent meal (none hot) and snacks like fruit and chips that are perfect to take with. Nice view.
Si bien no es de los mejores lounges vale la pena el acceso. Una buena opción para escalas largas. Tiene Buenas duchas pero hay que reservarlas al llegar.
A little crowded and a few outlets didn’t work. Food was better than expected. Nice drink selection and the bartender was friendly.
This is not a place to rest or stop or do whatever..no kidding.... some ghetto stuff..I'm not sure if that word is allowed to be used but maybe spend money across in the Delta Sky Club.. not here.
Honestly after just coming from a Centurion Lounge I literally spent five minutes here before walking out in disgust. Don't waste your time walking all the way here from the other terminals.
Decent lounge with drinks, snacks, wifi, and lots of seating. Nice showers and bathrooms.
More crowded than I would have preferred, but not bad.
This is awful food. Like worse than the worst free food at a horrible hotel. Raspberry chipotle? Is this a joke? People are nice. Bar is big. Chairs are okay. Power outlets abound.
Nice place. Not as busy as Delta lounges. Great drink selection and decent food.
Nice lounge. Really crowded though.
Was flying southwest out of C terminal but ended up trying this. Worth detour - free snacks and tiny  sandwiches and good selection of wine, beers and alcohol.
Front desk and bar staff is so sweet. Food is good for snack/light lunch. Showers and bathroom were very clean. Free booze as promised. Plenty of seating in Monday afternoon.
Snooty woman at check in, as usual. The rest is decent. Your basic lounge. Nowhere to sleep and limited window seating. Showers are a plus and the bathrooms were very nice and clean at 6:15AM.
Crowded at 5pm on a Monday when I went - 90% full. The drinks were good, but the food was some simple sandwiches and hummus.
Bright light and clean with excellent service. Food is mediocre.
Food gone 1 hour prior to closing. I was reminded repeatedly that they were closing in 1 hour. Told that they don't carry ketchup, which I then found at the bar. Worst service I've ever seen.
Not bad but not great. I could not find a power outlet that worked so I left early to charge my phone. People were nice and drinks were readily available. I give it 2.5 stars.

Lounge is a great option if you don't have access to DL SC. Lunch selection is all cold with hard boiled eggs, cheese, and veggies with hummus. Bar is good. Easy, quick ride to F from other concourses.
Friendly and helpful staff, basic food items with soup, sandwiches, chips. A bit crowded both times we've been here. Showers are decent.
Lunch offerings were good with sandwiches, soup, salads. Free drinks! Breakfast is pretty lame. Staff is efficient but the seats need deep cleaning! Plenty of plugs but some of them don't work.
Crowded New Years Eve.  Difficult to find a place to sit. Lots of families with children.  Many chairs dirty. Good snack selection, but mediocre food quality.  No towels in restroom. Rating: Meh.

The lounge is nice, but several powerports aren't working & clean dishes are hard to find. While the snack selection seems to be replenished often, one of the coffee makers is down. Many kids in here.
The food was picked over, but the drinks were good. And the service was great.
Shower felt amazing. Best food selection in ATL. Lots of space. Not crowded. Highly recommend.
Bar was nice. Lots of people, but didn't feel crowded. Chicken salad wraps and tomato soup were on point.
Great service + servers going around taking orders. Average food options -- finger food and soups. It's a small lounge with cramped seating, but had no trouble finding a lounge chair to sit in.
Friendly staff, nice bar and good finger foods. Worth trip to F if you don't have access to anything else.
Worth the train ride out to F, but don't expect too much. Minimal food spread at lunch time. Fairly empty and quiet - a good place to get some work done.
Worthwhile train ride over here. I sat at the bar the entire time and kept the cocktails coming (included). I enjoyed hummus, pita bread, and some finger sandwiches. Great service!
Lounge was good, I only sat at the bar getting Long Islands so I can't say much, tried to take a shower but it was occupied, only 2 showers available, but other than that I had a blast!
Solid lounge in Atlanta. Usual morning fare with cereals, yogurt, muffins, etc.  Ample seating. Business center. Showers. Very clean as far as I could tell!
Very reasonable option in ATL. Visited in the morning. Basic breakfast with cereals, yogurt, fruit, and bagels. Not crowded. Quite clean. Better than most Delta clubs.
Very clean lounge with some of the most exceptionally pleasant and friendly service I have experienced in a lounge. Very pleased.
Here at noon on a weekday. Plenty of seats. Only food is hummus, pita bread, and chips. No bartender to be seen. Will probably head to Sky Club across the hall instead.
I don't expect much on a domestic trip. Found this lounge to be worth the trip to Concourse F.
NO PLACE TO NAP HERE.
Plenty of space to relax, nice selection of food and beverages.
Best Priority Pass lounge I've ever been to. Great food, great view, and amazing service! Don't have to leave my chair to get a drink! (Or refills!)
Bartender Irina makes fantastic Bloody Mary's. Very quiet lounge, bar is a little uncomfortable and the view is only so-so. Bathrooms very private and clean. Overall, very OK.
Basic lounge with decent snacks but no real food. Service was good. Furniture was meh.
Like all Club locations, this one in ATL is fresh, modern and spacious. Minimal breakfast but much more substantial dinner choices. Free cocktails. Even have showers, a huge plus. Worth the detour!
Awesome spot. Fast Wifi. Lots of power. Couldn't ask for more.
Decent size lounge with modern furniture. Soup and sandwich offerings. Good variety of complimentary alcoholic beverages. Staff is very friendly and helpful.
Came at 2ish pm. Decent food selection, brisk service, ample space. Wish they had lids for their to-go cups!
This is a "fresh" lounge, not too big but still a looker. Good snack options (salads and veggies), clean...but really crowded during the day.
Pretty good lounge but far from all domestic terminals. Limited food options as with all domestic lounges.
Not many food options before noon, however, a good quiet place to have a coffee and check email. Evening had a much better food selection and the bar is well stocked.
Breakfast food is very limited, cold only. I did not stay long. Delta lounge next door has better breakfast and is a nicer lounge.
Decent lounge. New furnishings. Can get crowded as it is serving most intl flts except Delta.
Pleasant lounge, plenty of light snacks, full bar, was worth hopping on inter-terminal train since currently no alternatives.
Good selection of free alcoholic drinks and cold food, as well as some hot soups. Friendly staff, lots of space, and decent Wi-Fi made for a pleasant stay.
Nice, quiet lounge in international terminal. May be a long trek from your domestic gate. Good drink selection, decent service and seats, and good finger foods but served late (2:30pm).
Food is sparse before 2:30 but lounge is very clean; WELL stocked bar and staff is exceptional. ??
Great lounge compared to US domestic airline lounges. Reasonably sized, friendly staff, and more importantly, more substantial food like sandwiches.
Plenty of options for food. Kind of far from other clubs.
Don't waste your time coming to this lounge before 5pm if you're looking for something to eat. Just a few snack items with nothing more substantial than pita and hummus before then.
